msgid "Detected errors include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:70
msgid "Non-existing commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:71
msgid "Reading from or appending to a non-existing file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:72
msgid "Incorrect use of output redirects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:73
msgid "Mismatched parenthesis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:75
msgid ""
"To customize the syntax highlighting, you can set the environment variables "
"listed in the :ref:`Variables for changing highlighting colors <variables-"
"color>` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:77
msgid ""
"Fish also provides pre-made color themes you can pick with :doc:`fish_config "
"<cmds/fish_config>`. Running just ``fish_config`` opens a browser interface, "
"or you can use ``fish_config theme`` in the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:79
msgid "For example, to disable nearly all coloring::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:81
msgid "fish_config theme choose none"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:83
msgid "Or, to see all themes, right in your terminal::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:85
msgid "fish_config theme show"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:90
msgid "Syntax highlighting variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:92
msgid ""
"The colors used by fish for syntax highlighting can be configured by "
"changing the values of various variables. The value of these variables can "
"be one of the colors accepted by the :doc:`set_color <cmds/set_color>` "
"command. The modifier switches accepted by ``set_color`` like ``--bold``, "
"``--dim``, ``--italics``, ``--reverse`` and ``--underline`` are also "
"accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:95
msgid "Example: to make errors highlighted and red, use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../interactive.rst:97
msgid "set fish_color_error red --bold"
msgstr ""

